caption: I have never had a bad meal at Augie's!!!  Thrifty Thursday's are great on the pocketbook and you won't leave hungry.   Staff are knowledgeable & efficient!!   If you are visiting downtown Springfield, this should be in your top 3 places to eat.   The other two would be Mangia & Maldaners.  great
Lamb is some of the best in town
The Thursday three course option was excellent. The food was original and stupendous.

During a weekend visit to Springfield, someone we met on the street recommended Augie's. We four had a SUPERB meal while snow blew furiously outside. One in our party has several diet restrictions--no problem: a wonderful, piping hot dinner appeared, made to order. Our lovely server was gracious and attentive.
Ok
Quiet atmosphere, great food, well made drinks.
The whole staff was kind and the atmosphere was relaxing! Thank you!

We travel from St. Louis and this is our first stop after the hotel! The food is devine and service by Shelby and Kim top notch! Never been disappointed in the years we have been visiting! Scallops and filet amazing!
Went there for lunch. The lunch options were plentiful. The food and staff were amazing. The cost was very reasonable for the quantity and quality of food served.

We were visiting from out of town and decided on this for our late night dinner spot, and so glad we did! The service was excellent and food was amazing. Even though we were still eating and it was almost closing time, we did not feel rushed and the server even offered dessert and coffee once we finished eating. Would definitely visit again.
Great lunch stop.  Daughter had lobster bisque and I  had the smoked salmon on pumpernickel with a fresh mixed baby greens salad.
Most delicious steak ever!! Service was fantastic!
I wish I would have started going to this place sooner in my life,  it is so good...the best quality you can get. Great service too!
Augies is FIRE, some of the best food you can get in Springfield. Definitely check it out!
Limited options for vegetarian.
This place is always delicious and an extraordinary value! Don't miss it! Just had the shrimp and grits! Tasty!
Always love this place!  One of my favorite go to lunch spots!

Nothing short of excellent! The food was very good, with several unusual offerings; and the service was great also. We went for lunch, but Augie's would be ideal for a nice dinner as well. If you are visiting, Augie's should be on your short list.

I always enjoy the great service and wonderful food.  The steaks and seafood specials are top notch.  The ever changing Taco's are a wonderful appetizer.  The salads change so order the Goat Cheese or Poached Pear when they are on the menu.

Lovely place for any meal. All of the food was very fresh, flavorful, and beautifully plated. Highly recommend the lobster bisque. The waiter was friendly and attentive. Our food was out in well under 10 minutes, which is a miracle considering the high quality of the dishes. This place will definitely be a stop the next time I'm in Springfield!

Thrifty Thursday was a great menu and delicious food.  I've always loved Augie's caesar salad and it was delicious as always.  Great service and delicious warm tools as well.  This has been a favorite of mine for years and hadn't been in a while and it did not disappoint.
We had the salmon, chicken, steak, black bean cakes, crab cakes. Everyone liked their dishes. Server was professional.

Very good dinners, smiles and compliments all around, dessert was special.  Nice creativity constructing the meals, presentation and combination of "sides" with the entree.  Dessert, you need.  Enjoy!
One of Springfields best.
Pricey but good food,not much soda option's.
Delicious food and friendly staff.

Very cool place overlooking the old Illinois capital in an area that's fun to walk around and explore different spots. The food was good and the prices weren't outrageous. You'll feel comfortable wearing a suit and tie or jeans and a t-shirt. The menu changes a lot so you'll find new things to eat.
Excellent food, great service, wonderful Bourbon list. Will definitely revisit when in town.
Aggies has a great menu and good service. I always enjoy eating here.
Delicious
Some of the best food in the city. Very consistent. You will enjoy.
Always the best place to go for great service, food adjusted to your taste, and locally grown menu items.

Extremely quick lunch service, beautiful setup, and friendly staff.  The "Shut up and Eat" was salmon BLT: huge, pretty, and delicious.  Definately will come back.

We went on a Thrifty Thursday and the food and service was outstanding!

Never disappointed!
Very small menu so no very much to choose from. Makes me think that the cooks or cook has limited cooking ability.

What a delicious meal! My hubby had the steak special and I had the salmon. Both were amazing. We also had appetizers and dessert, also yummy! I would be happy to go back anytime and would recommend it highly.

It was a nice little hideaway in the middle of downtown. Parking can be tricky but worth the effort. I had the roasted beet salad with feta cheese and it was delicious. It had an apple cider vinaigrette that I really enjoyed. I would definitely go back!

Our favorite restaurant. We have been coming here since 1991. They always have the best of food. The staff is attentive, know about wines, is articulated, eager to please. The food is excellent, well prepared. They never disappoint. Springfield is lucky to have this restaurant. Kudos to you!!
Great lunch.  Fast and friendly service.
Very nice atmosphere, but I really didn't enjoy  the steak gyro
Great food, great service and new specials regularly.
The place was packed on a Thursday night.
First time eating here. Perhaps one of the best salads and steaks I've ever eaten.
Amazing recipes and the food here is just as good as the view
I like this place for lunch.  It is a great alternative to processed and fried.  They do a great job.  There is a classy ambiance and the staff is professional.  Would highly recommend.

I probably looked homeless I had been working all day building shelves for our warehouse and asked my wife where to meet for dinner.  We had seen the sign, Augie's casual dining but when I stepped in and the man at the door was wearing a tux I tried to leave. He stopped me at the door and told us to sit down and we had a great time.  My kids ate duck for the first time and all the food was good. I understood later that man at the door is the owner and a more gracious man you will not find and find food to boot. I felt out of place walking in but they made me feel right at home, thank you.  Don't forget to click like if the review helps
The food was great and the menu options were unique. They also offered a wide range of drinks. I highly suggest the goat cheese and prosciutto salad!
We always have a great meal at Augie's...
Food is always excellent with a great atmosphere.

Fantastic food and even better service.  Top notch.  I had the Philly cheese steak flat bread and the seafood chowder.  This is no skimpy chowder, it was packed with big chunks of seafood.  I was really impressed.  Way to go guys.
My favorite restaurant in Springfield!
Lovely quaint atmosphere. Great for date night. I have dreamt about the salmon entree. It was SO delicious.
Great food. Nice comfy slightly formal place

I love Augie's! If you want high end dining and top notch wines this is the place to go. I really appreciate how their exotic menu is still very palatable to those of us who were raised on traditional american foods.
The good was really good, it was difficult choosing what to order as everything is looks so good. You won't be disappointed if you eat here!
Awesome!!
Great food
Usually go for the Elk Burger, which is a seasonal item not currently available. No worries, there menu is loaded with lots more options. Can't go wrong at Augie's
Great food and atmosphere for a date or with family.
Always have a great meal every time we visit. The service is wonderful and the staff is always friendly.
My favorite gourmet place in Springfield

Great quality food. The chef is imaginative and all of our food was fantastic. Our server, Matt, was very well versed in the entire menu and personable. We look forward to our next trip to Springfield so we can indulge again.
Fav restaurant in the downtown Springfield locale.   Many great menu choices and a solid wine list!
Delicious and great service

Busy place, but I was able to walk in and get a seat at the bar where I could eat some dinner. My bartender was very friendly & poured a great cocktail. I had the lobster bisque & it was very good (note: it's only $5 & we're in Springfield, so don't go looking for whole pieces of lobster.) Then I got the pan seared/ cooked filet, which came with fingerling  potatoes & roasted brussels sprouts, it was dynamite! Finished with a solid key lime pie.
Food was good but not great and seemed somewhat overpriced.

This may seem like a hole in the wall, but they really try to give a show of a more high-scale dining experience. Whether it is high-scale or not, I couldn’t care less, because this food is good. I was able to try their Augie’s Front Burger (seen in the picture) with the Caesar salad and my, oh my, I was not disappointed.  This particular burger option comes with what they call “Chef calls it daily” (and several other menu items have this as well), which means that the chef takes his/her creative liberties with that particular food item on a day by day basis – so, it may not be the same the next time you order it. The menu even contains an item labeled, get this, “Shut up and eat”, no description, nothing, just a full meal of whatever the chef decides to put in front of you (check out their lunch menu and see for yourself). I’ll have to admit, I’m a little intrigued by this idea…  Anyway, I digress. The chef’s options for my burger this day included sautéed peppers and onions and I can’t remember what cheese, but believe me, as this burger also included your standard lettuce, pickles, tomato, and onion on the side…I did not need to add those at all. The flavors from what the chef ‘called’ were more than enough. Plus, I ordered the burger medium rare and that’s exactly what it was – these cooks know their stuff.  I am going back here and I urge you to try this place out – you will not be disappointed.

Absolutely unbelievable mouth watering food. It's well thought out and paired with perfection with really interesting sides and salads! Service is exemplary! It is a small restaurant but it is mighty!!
Beautiful restaurant. The ambience and food was beyond exquisite. Thanks for making us feel welcomed to Springfield.
Lobster Bisque was great.  As was the rest of the meal.
Lunch service was  HORRIBLE and the grilled quesadilla tasted line salmon because it was all groomed on the same grill... NOT pleased
Excellent! Great desserts too!

Popped in today while walking around downtown for a little historical site seeing. I had my two puppies with me and I am so glad I stopped! I had the lobster bisque, duck and sangria. Well worth the price and sitting out on their patio was so peaceful and beautiful! My server Alexa was super attentive and wonderful and kept my glass (and the puppy bowl!) full. I would highly recommend both Alexa and the restaurant for sure.
Incredible
fabulous meal and service!

As my dining companion put it, it's remarkable to find a menu so exceptional paired with a decor that...isn't. I've been here a few times. The only food-related disappointment I've experienced was with the fish tacos that were on special last time I was there. Otherwise great.
As usual, outstanding service and excellent food. 5 stars isn't enough.
The waitress mostly ignored the table. Didn't finally get bread until after the entree arrived.
Friendly wait staff, yummy food, and warm ambience.  One of my favorite places - Springfield can be hard pickings!
Nice place for lunch - great service, food. Cuyler - excellent server!
Very good

Excellent food!

I ordered the roasted beet salad with chocolate tomatoes. The lettuce and dressing were good but the tomatoes were Not chocolate tomatoes ( I grow them) and the beets were from a can. Waiter was nice .
Tasty, good service and very well prepared food.
Nice atmosphere, but a little bit pricey.
Good location, clean, friendly staff, decent atmosphere, food tastes good. But I asked for a medium rare burger, got a well done one, same for the person sitting next to me, in our large group.
Amazing mixed drinks, great food. Mediocre atmosphere, partially friendly staff, small tables.
This is a casual place with good food. I had a cup of soup that was very good and a burger. All the food was good and worth a visit. Try the lemonade because it is awesome.
Our favorite restaurant in Springfield.   Experienced staff and great food.  Lovely for a nice dinner out or special occasion.
Always a great meal here. Food prepared fresh with outstanding pairing of sauces on the dishes. Homemade pasta, local beef. Perfect!

This is the best steakhouse in Springfield IL. The service is very good and the view of the state capital from the top floor is incredible. The place is expensive and at par with any place in St Louis or Chicago.

As a first time customer, I wasn't quite sure what to expect. But my experience was quite nice. My server (Matt) was attentive, professional,  and amusing! My only issue was my steak was ordered medium rare, and it was delivered medium/slightly well done. I chose not to send it back as it was Valentine's Day and knew the staff had had a very long busy day already, and it was still delicious............The fried goat cheese salad is absolute ambrosia, wow! Great local restaurant serving something other than the usual burger, fries and horseshoe fare downtown. Outdoor seating in the summer, great staff, pricier than other downtown locations though.

This restaurant is on the 30th floor of the Wyndham Hotel in Springfield. We arrived just before sunset, and the views are spectacular. Denise greeted us and seated us. She was so kind - we had spoken by phone when she called to confirm our reservation, and it she was just as charming in person. Rick was our knowledgeable waiter,...

The healthy options abound even on a menu with good bar food. The salads are delicious and large, the salmon and mahi are good, and the workout grill is healthy and filling. I also love the not-so-healthy parmesan fries with avocado ranch dipping sauce. YUM!
Awesome place

By far the best original cuisine in Springfield. The chef de cuisine is outstanding at what he does and the service staff is knowledgeable and friendly. Steak cuts can sometimes be an adventure but everything else is on point. Would not eat anywhere else if I visited for the night.

Great atmosphere, service and food, price was well aligned with what one would expect for the dining experience. I had the taco appetizer, followed by one of the evening special entries: a seafood combination of cod, shrimp and mussels. I finished with Creme brûlée for dessert. The meal was delicious. My preference in dinner drink is red wine, 2 glasses of Aviary Cab, finished off the evening with great cup of coffee. Total bill with tax: $69.72. All-in-all well worth the price.

My favorite restaurant in Springfield, ALWAYS good.  Geoff Jr.

Not a bad place if you don't mind paying top dollar(for the area) for food that is frozen. This places freezes just about everything that can be frozen, and the owner is an absolute nut job. I would avoid this place like the plague.

Got taken here by my brother in law who touted it to be the best. Ordered the house special steak cooked "blue", waiter came back saying I wouldn't like the results so change to a filet. I'm not sure if the cook was mad at the waiter or didn't know what blue was but when my meal arrived the filet was burnt to a crisp. Quite possibly the worse steak I've had, but I did't have the heart to say anything as it might embarrass my brother in law. Also the meals were  overpriced. Needless to say I won't be going back. Stay Away!!!

One of our fave places to dine in Springfield. We go out of our way to make the trip there any time we are in town. Food is great, ambiance is super and service is fantastic. We love that they use local farms to source their food. Highly recommend.
